# Deploy & environment

## Split deploy

| Service | Host | Build / start |
|---------|------|---------------|
| Frontend | **Vercel** | `npm run build` → output `dist/` |
| API | **Render** | `npx tsx server/src/index.ts` |

## Critical env vars

**Vercel (set at BUILD time — Vite embeds these):**

- `VITE_API_URL` — **required in production** (e.g. `https://your-api.onrender.com`)
- `VITE_APP_VERSION`, feature flags — see `.env.example`

**Render:**

- `PORT` — auto-set by Render

If `VITE_API_URL` is empty, API calls hit the static host and fail (404).

## PWA & assets

- Run `npm run icons` before release — commits `public/icons/`, favicon, apple-touch-icon
- Service Worker registers only in **production** (`import.meta.env.PROD`)
- Install button needs HTTPS deploy; localhost dev often has no `beforeinstallprompt`

## Do not commit

- `.env`, `.env.local`
- `server/data/db.json` (local dev DB with tokens) — use `db.json.example`

## API storage note

Server uses `server/data/db.json` (file). On Render free tier, data resets on redeploy unless persistent disk is added.
